<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1172> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1172" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire), and on Longus, cf. 256; Polyb. 1.39.15; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.10.2, with the cognomen Vulsco; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.15; see Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f. Both Consuls served in Sicily with fleet and army, but failed with considerable losses in their attempt to capture Lilybaeum (Polyb. 1.41.1-6, and 42.7-48.11; Diod. 24.1.1-4; Oros. 4.10.2; Zon. 8.15)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1143> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1143" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354 (Longo et Rugulo); Fast. Hyd. (Vulsone et Decio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Manlius, Act. Tr.; Polyb. 1.26.11; Liv. 29.28.5; Iustin. 41.4.3; Dio fr. 43.20, and Zon. 8.12; Eutrop. 2.21; Oros. 4.8.9; see Degrassi 42f., 116, 434f. Caedicius died in office (Fast. Cap.), but Manlius and Regulus, the Consul Suffectus, defeated a large Carthaginian fleet off Sicily, refitted at Messana, and made a landing in Africa, whence Manlius brought home prisoners and booty (Polyb. 1.25-29; Eutrop. 2.21; Ampel. 46; Oros. 4.8.6-9; Zon. 8.12-13; cf. Diod. 23.11), and celebrated a naval triumph (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 548)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10149> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10149" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Naval Triumph de Poeneis. MRR I.208, Itgenshorst no. 134, Rich no. 133." .
